Text: This week has been fairly productive, although I'm currently juggling upcoming deadlines with all of my course work but I'm on track to get it all completed on time.
We met with Mimi on Tuesday to discuss the current progress of the project and what our plans were for the week.
We asked him again for the content for the pages, but unfortunately we still haven't received this so we will try again.
In the mean time we will just pad out the website with basic information and I went to the museum myself this week to gather some photos of the exhibits to use on the website.
It has also been decided that we will focus on using QR codes instead of NFC, just to make sure the web page works well and the right kind of NFC tags seem hard to acquire.
As for the current progress on the website we've made steady progress with implementing the designs that Nene and Yoko have created.
We have a responsive page designed for mobile (but still looks okay for desktop) for the hub page of the animal attic.
It also took me some time to figure out how to implement a modal for a video pop-up.
I eventually find that bootstrap includes the use of modals which makes it much easier.
It has been at least 5 years since I had last written a web page and it has taken a while for me to remember how it all works (still have a lot to figure out).
So progress has been a little slower there as I've had to try refresh myself on how to do it.
As the team leader I feel I failed a little bit this week.
There has been a bit of a disconnect between what the group members have been working on and some of the work was repeated.

Once I realized this was happening I made sure to let everyone know and planned out our Trello page more carefully and made sure everyone was aware of it and was actively trying to use it, so that people weren't working on 2 different instances of the same task.
I've also scheduled us some collaborative work times, so we can all work at the same time and be aware of what each other is doing and be available to help each other.
This next week will be the test to see if this was effective or if another measure will be needed.
Even with the issues over the week, we are still on track and meeting our goals.
Our goals for this week were to have a completed design and to start implementing that which we managed to achieve.
We also managed to add in videos and audio to the pages which on our timeline was schedules for next week.
Although they do need tweaked to work a little smoother.
The only thing missing from the mentioned goals in last weeks blog was ordering NFC tags, but we've moved to focusing on QR codes so that is now null.

Our goals for the upcoming week: Populate the pages with more information (hopefully the content provided by Mimi)Upload the pages to the museums serverCreate and test QR codesFine tune the audio/video controls
Overall
